Want to know the QUICKEST way to creating REAL momentum & change in your life?? ⁣
⁣
Mel Robbins actually says it best, but we TOTALLY agree with her, so here it is ... ⁣
⁣
... you have to start intentionally acting like the person you want to become. 💖⁣
⁣
Think about the goals you want to achieve throughout your life, whether they’re BIG or small, now take yourself out of the equation for a second and imagine who the type of person is that actually hits all those goals.⁣
⁣
💖 What qualities do they have?⁣
💖 What do their habits/routines look like?⁣
💖 How do they operate from day to day?⁣
⁣
⁣
Describe them in detail, jot down your notes on one of the blank pages in your Daily Grind Planner, and start acting as if that’s already YOU today!!!⁣
⁣
It’s powerful mindset shifts like this paired with the Daily Grind planning system that is guaranteed to help you get closer to living your BEST, most fulfilled life! ⁣
⁣

Disney Bar Hop 🍹
One of our favourite things to do in Disney World is explore new restaurants that we haven’t yet experienced .
We love starting out at a random bar and going where the wind takes us. 

First up ..three bridges bar at Coronado 🍹( villa del Lago ) 
I had the Spanish margarita, and we shared a couple of nibbles . This spot was a little bit disappointing because I was so excited to experience the atmosphere . It was a lot more chaotic that I thought it was gonna be . Should we give it another chance?

From there we jumped over to one of our favs 
🍸 Dhalias at the Grand Destino ( walking distance from three bridges ) they make really great Manhattan’s and martinis, and we love their chips as well as the artichoke app. 

🎷 we couldn’t make it all the way home without stopping at Scat cats at the port, Orleans, French Quarter. It’s such a hidden gem and you literally feel like you’re in New Orleans. You can also have a cocktail while enjoying some beignets. They even have booze injected ones 🤣 

we honestly had the best time hopping around and we would totally love your suggestions on any spots that we should try next !! 👇🏼🥂

Soooo… Can we just go back to posting cute pics like we use to? 🐰 

Seriously … what do you prefer ? 
Photos or reels ? Or are you just over it all? 

I’ll be honest , I kind of feel like reels and short videos have kind of gotten out of hand, and I would love if there was just a great balance of both. 

I miss the good old days when it was just real life photos and videos you couldn’t edit. Oh , and of course when we didn’t feel the need to embarrass others or ourselves just to get views. 🫠 ( I don’t think I’ll ever be able to wrap my head around that.) 

As per usual, I’m just gonna be super transparent and honest … 
I’ve kinda decided that moving forward I’m just going to be my most creative self and if that comes out as a video cool , if it comes out of the photo awesome . 
And if no one likes it, that’s OK too . 

Instagram started for me as a creative outlet and I’d really like it to go back to that . 

I don’t ever feel like I lost that with my vlogs and videos on my channel but I do feel like I lost that on my other platforms. 

So starting today I’m putting creativity first. Moving forward, I think I’ll be happiest by doing what fills my cup and not trying to chase someone else’s agenda or what’s considered “cool” or “trending”. 

Chances are that will fall between the lines of decorating and Cleaning, my dog , habits and routines, motivation, my own real life and romanticizing even the littlest things we might take for granted. 

So if that’s your jam … stick around 🌸

An easy Christmas DIY project.
🌲❄️ 
1. You’ll need a bucket or a pail. I found these metal ones that had Holiday theme. They are from @canadiantire 
2. Make sure to secure the pails with some rocks at the bottom feel free to add some water because it’ll freeze and that can keep everything sturdy as well.
3. Gather some branches , twigs and sticks to add to the bucket.
4. Add in some real or faux poinsettias.
5. Accessorize with fairy lights or a cardinal like I did.
 
❤️❄️ enjoy all winter long !
